    hadithEnglish:
      ' Narrated Sa`id bin Al-Musaiyab:\n\n`Ali and `Uthman differed regarding Hajj-at-Tamattu` while they were at Usfan (a familiar place near Mecca). `Ali said, I see you want to forbid people to do a thing that the Prophet (ﷺ) did? When `Ali saw that, he assumed Ihram for both Hajj and `Umra.',
