    hadithEnglish:
      ' Narrated Tawus:\n\nIbn `Abbas said, Allahs Messenger (ﷺ) forbade the selling of foodstuff before its measuring and transferring into ones possession. I asked Ibn `Abbas, How is that? Ibn `Abbas replied, It will be just like selling money for money, as the foodstuff has not been handed over to the first purchaser who is the present seller.',
